cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about compressing convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for biomedical image segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new compression scheme based on predicting network accuracy for different sizes, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. Additionally, the paper involves optimizing network size and accuracy, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The compression scheme also involves selecting a multiplicative factor, which is a mathematical optimization problem, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category. Finally, the paper is about biomedical image analysis, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
